.TH "snd_ctl_boolean_mono_info" 9 "snd_ctl_boolean_mono_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ctl_boolean_mono_info \- Helper function for a standard boolean info callback with a mono channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_ctl_boolean_mono_info
.BI "(struct snd_kcontrol *kcontrol "  ","
.BI "struct snd_ctl_elem_info *uinfo "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kcontrol" 12
the kcontrol instance
.IP "uinfo" 12
info to store
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a function that can be used as info callback for a standard
boolean control with a single mono channel.
